Wild Horseradish.description: A spicy root found in the spring.

Daffodil.description: A traditional spring flower that makes a nice gift.

Leek.description: A tasty relative of the onion.

Dandelion.description: Not the prettiest flower, but the leaves make a good salad.

Parsnip.description: A spring tuber closely related to the carrot. It has an earthy taste and is full of nutrients.

Lumber.description: A versatile resource used for building and fuel.

Emerald.description: A precious stone with a brilliant green color.

Ruby.description: A precious stone that is sought after for its rich color and beautiful luster.

Topaz.description: Fairly common but still prized for its beauty.

Banana Sapling.description: Takes 28 days to produce a mature Banana tree. Bears fruit in the summer, or all year round when planted on Ginger Island.

Trimmed Lucky Purple Shorts.description: Purple silk shorts trimmed in luxurious gold...

Golden Walnut.description: To the parrots of Ginger Island, this nut is the finest delicacy.

Prismatic Shard.description: A very rare and powerful substance with unknown origins.

Cave Carrot.description: A starchy snack found in caves. It helps miners work longer.

Secret Note.description: It's old and crumpled, but if you look closely you can make out the details...

Quartz.description: A clear crystal commonly found in caves and mines.

Fire Quartz.description: A glowing red crystal commonly found near hot lava.

Frozen Tear.description: A crystal fabled to be the frozen tears of a yeti.

Earth Crystal.description: A resinous substance found near the surface.

Coconut.description: A seed of the coconut palm. It has many culinary uses.

Cactus Fruit.description: The sweet fruit of the prickly pear cactus.

Torch.description: Provides a modest amount of light.

Spirit Torch.description: It's unclear where the blue color comes from...

Dwarf Scroll I.description: A yellowed scroll of parchment filled with dwarven script. This one's tied with a red bow.

Dwarf Scroll II.description: A yellowed scroll of parchment filled with dwarven script. This one's tied with a green ribbon.

Dwarf Scroll III.description: A yellowed scroll of parchment filled with dwarven script. This one's tied with a blue rope.

Dwarf Scroll IV.description: A yellowed scroll of parchment filled with dwarven script. This one's tied with a golden chain.

Chipped Amphora.description: An ancient vessel made of ceramic material. Used to transport both dry and wet goods.

Arrowhead.description: A crudely fashioned point used for hunting.

Lost Book.description: Writings from a wide variety of time periods.

Ancient Doll.description: An ancient doll covered in grime. This doll may have been used as a toy, a decoration, or a prop in some kind of ritual.

Elvish Jewelry.description: Dirty but still beautiful. On the side is a flowing script thought by some to be the ancient language of the elves. No Elvish bones have ever been found.

Chewing Stick.description: Ancient people chewed on these to keep their teeth clean.

Ornamental Fan.description: This exquisute fan most likely belonged to a noblewoman. Historians believe that the valley was a popular sixth-era vacation spot for the wealthy.

Dinosaur Egg.description: A giant dino egg... The entire shell is still intact!

Rare Disc.description: A heavy black disc studded with peculiar red stones. When you hold it, you're overwhelmed with a feeling of dread.

Ancient Sword.description: It's the remains of an ancient sword. Most of the blade has turned to rust, but the hilt is very finely crafted.

Rusty Spoon.description: A plain old spoon, probably ten years old. Not very interesting.

Rusty Spur.description: An old spur that was once attached to a cowboy's boot. People must have been raising animals in this area for many generations.

Rusty Cog.description: A well preserved cog that must have been part of some ancient machine. This could be dwarven technology.

Chicken Statue.description: It's a statue of a chicken on a bronze base. The ancient people of this area must have been very fond of chickens.

Ancient Seed.description: It's a dry old seed from some ancient plant. By all appearances it's long since dead...

Prehistoric Tool.description: Some kind of gnarly old digging tool.

Dried Starfish.description: A starfish from the primordial ocean. It's an unusually pristine specimen!

Anchor.description: It may have belonged to ancient pirates.

Glass Shards.description: A mixture of glass shards smoothed by centuries of ocean surf. These could have belonged to an ancient mosaic or necklace.

Bone Flute.description: It's a prehistoric wind instrument carved from an animal's bone. It produces an eerie tone.

Prehistoric Handaxe.description: One of the earliest tools employed by humans. This "crude" tool was created by striking one rock with another to form a sharp edge.

Dwarvish Helm.description: It's one of the helmets commonly worn by dwarves. The thick metal plating protects them from falling debris and stalactites.

Dwarf Gadget.description: It's a piece of the advanced technology once known to the dwarves. It's still glowing and humming, but you're unable to understand how it works.

Ancient Drum.description: It's a drum made from wood and animal skin. It has a low, reverberating tone.

Golden Mask.description: A creepy golden mask probably used in an ancient magic ritual. A socket in the forehead contains a large purple gemstone.

Golden Relic.description: It's a golden slab with heiroglyphs and pictures emblazoned onto the front.

Anchovy.description: A small silver fish found in the ocean.

Tuna.description: A large fish that lives in the ocean.

Bream.description: A fairly common river fish that becomes active at night.

Largemouth Bass.description: A popular fish that lives in lakes.

Smallmouth Bass.description: A freshwater fish that is very sensitive to pollution.

Rainbow Trout.description: A freshwater trout with colorful markings.

Salmon.description: Swims upstream to lay its eggs.

Walleye.description: A freshwater fish caught at night.

Perch.description: A freshwater fish of the winter.

Catfish.description: An uncommon fish found in streams.

Pike.description: A freshwater fish that's difficult to catch.

Red Mullet.description: Long ago these were kept as pets.

Red Snapper.description: A popular fish with a nice red color.

Squid.description: A deep sea creature that can grow to enormous size.

Seaweed.description: It can be used in cooking.

Sea Cucumber.description: A slippery, slimy creature found on the ocean floor.

Super Cucumber.description: A rare, purple variety of sea cucumber.

Ghostfish.description: A pale, blind fish found in underground lakes.

Stonefish.description: A bizarre fish that's shaped like a brick.

Crimsonfish.description: Lives deep in the ocean but likes to lay its eggs in the warm summer water.

Angler.description: Uses a bioluminescent dangler to attract prey.

Ice Pip.description: A rare fish that thrives in extremely cold conditions.

Lava Eel.description: It can somehow survive in pools of red-hot lava.

Legend.description: The king of all fish! They said he'd never be caught.

Sandfish.description: It tries to hide using camouflage.

Scorpion Carp.description: It's like a regular carp but with a sharp stinger.

Treasure Chest.description: Wow, it's loaded with treasure! This is sure to fetch a good price.

Joja Cola.description: The flagship product of Joja corporation.

Driftwood.description: A piece of wood from the sea.

Broken Glasses.description: It looks like someone lost their glasses. They're busted.

Broken CD.description: It's a JojaNet 2.0 trial CD. They must've made a billion of these things.

Large Egg.description: It's an uncommonly large brown egg!

Hay.description: Dried grass used as animal food.

Large Milk.description: A large jug of cow's milk.

Green Bean.description: A juicy little bean with a cool, crisp snap.

Cauliflower.description: Valuable, but slow-growing. Despite its pale color, the florets are packed with nutrients.

Ornate Necklace.description: A fancy necklace found in the water outside of the bath house. It's still wet...

Baked Fish.description: Baked fish on a bed of herbs.

Complete Breakfast.description: You'll feel ready to take on the world!

Pizza.description: It's popular for all the right reasons.

Glazed Yams.description: Sweet and satisfying... The sugar gives it a hint of caramel.

Pancakes.description: A double stack of fluffy, soft pancakes.

Salmon Dinner.description: The lemon spritz makes it special.

Pepper Poppers.description: Spicy breaded peppers filled with cheese.

Chocolate Cake.description: Rich and moist with a thick fudge icing.

Pink Cake.description: There's little heart candies on top.

Sashimi.description: Raw fish sliced into thin pieces.

Maki Roll.description: Fish and rice wrapped in seaweed.

Tortilla.description: Can be used as a vessel for food or eaten by itself.

Rice Pudding.description: It's creamy, sweet, and fun to eat.

Ice Cream.description: It's hard to find someone who doesn't like this.

Stuffing.description: Ahh... the smell of warm bread and sage.

Survival Burger.description: A convenient snack for the explorer.

Dish O' The Sea.description: This'll keep you warm in the cold sea air.

Miner's Treat.description: This should keep your energy up.

Roots Platter.description: This'll get you digging for more.

Sugar.description: Adds sweetness to pastries and candies. Too much can be unhealthy.

Wheat Flour.description: A common cooking ingredient made from crushed wheat seeds.

Garlic.description: Adds a wonderful zestiness to dishes. High quality garlic can be pretty spicy.

Kale.description: The waxy leaves are great in soups and stir frys.

Rhubarb.description: The stalks are extremely tart, but make a great dessert when sweetened.

Tomato.description: Rich and slightly tangy, the Tomato has a wide variety of culinary uses.

Morel.description: Sought after for its unique nutty flavor.

Blueberry.description: A popular berry reported to have many health benefits. The blue skin has the highest nutrient concentration.

Fiddlehead Fern.description: The young shoots are an edible specialty.

Hot Pepper.description: Fiery hot with a hint of sweetness.

Warp Totem: Desert.description: Warp directly to Calico Desert. Consumed on use.

Wheat.description: One of the most widely cultivated grains. Makes a great flour for breads and cakes.

Radish.description: A crisp and refreshing root vegetable with hints of pepper when eaten raw.

Seafoam Pudding.description: This briny pudding will really get you into the maritime mindset!

Flounder.description: It lives on the bottom, so both eyes are on top of its head.

Starfruit.description: An extremely juicy fruit that grows in hot, humid weather. Slightly sweet with a sour undertone.

Midnight Carp.description: This shy fish only feels comfortable at night.

Wilted Bouquet.description: A gift that shows you want to stop dating someone.

Bok Choy.description: The leafy greens and fibrous stalks are healthy and delicious.

Magic Rock Candy.description: A rare and powerful candy infused with the essence of the prismatic shard.

Yam.description: A starchy tuber with a lot of culinary versatility.

Chanterelle.description: A tasty mushroom with a fruity smell and slightly peppery flavor.

Cranberries.description: These tart red berries are a traditional winter food.

Holly.description: The leaves and bright red berries make a popular winter decoration.

Beet.description: A sweet and earthy root vegatable. As a bonus, the leaves make a great salad.

Cherry Bomb.description: Generates a small explosion. Stand back!

Mega Bomb.description: Generates a powerful explosion. Use with extreme caution.

Ostrich Egg.description: It may be the world's largest egg.

Alamite.description: Its distinctive fluorescence makes it a favorite among rock collectors.

Bixite.description: A dark metallic Mineral sought after for its cubic structure.

Baryte.description: The best specimens resemble a desert rose.

Calcite.description: This yellow crystal is speckled with shimmering nodules.

Dolomite.description: It can occur in coral reefs, often near an underwater volcano.

Esperite.description: The crystals glow bright green when stimulated.

Fluorapatite.description: Small amounts are found in human teeth.

Nekoite.description: The delicate shards form a tiny pink meadow.

Petrified Slime.description: This little guy may be 100,000 years old.

Thunder Egg.description: According to legend, angry thunder spirits would throw these stones at one another.

Ocean Stone.description: An old legend claims these stones are the mosaics of ancient mermaids.

Ghost Crystal.description: There is an aura of coldness around this crystal.

Tigerseye.description: A stripe of shimmering gold gives this gem a warm luster.

Jasper.description: When polished, this stone becomes attractively luminous. Prized by ancient peoples for thousands of years.

Opal.description: Its internal structure causes it to reflect a rainbow of light.

Fire Opal.description: A rare variety of opal, named for its red spots.

Celestine.description: Some early life forms had bones made from this.

Marble.description: A very popular material for sculptures and construction.

Sandstone.description: A common type of stone with red and brown striations.

Granite.description: A speckled Mineral that is commonly used in construction.

Limestone.description: A very common type of stone. It's not worth very much.

Soapstone.description: Because of its relatively soft consistency, this stone is very popular for carving.

Hematite.description: An iron-based Mineral with interesting magnetic properties.

Mudstone.description: A fine-grained rock made from ancient clay or mud.

Obsidian.description: A volcanic glass that forms when lava cools rapidly.

Slate.description: It's extremely resistant to water, making it a good roofing material.

Fairy Stone.description: An old miner's song suggests these are made from the bones of ancient fairies.

Star Shards.description: No one knows how these form. Some scientists claim that the microscopic structure displays unnatural regularity.

Prehistoric Scapula.description: Commonly known as a "shoulder blade"... It's unclear what species it belonged to.

Prehistoric Tibia.description: A thick and sturdy leg bone.

Prehistoric Skull.description: This is definitely a mammalian skull.

Skeletal Hand.description: It's a wonder all these ancient little pieces lasted so long.

Prehistoric Rib.description: Little gouge marks on the side suggest that this rib was someone's dinner.

Prehistoric Vertebra.description: A segment of some prehistoric creature's spine.

Skeletal Tail.description: It's pretty short for a tail.

Nautilus Fossil.description: This must've washed up ages ago from an ancient coral reef.

Palm Fossil.description: Palm Fossils are relatively common, but this happens to be a particularly well-preserved specimen.

Trilobite.description: A long extinct relative of the crab.

Artifact Spot.description: Uh... how did you get this in your inventory? Ape made a booboo.

Barbed Hook.description: Makes your catch more secure, causing the "fishing bar" to cling to your catch. Works best on slow, weak fish.

Lead Bobber.description: Adds weight to your "fishing bar", preventing it from bouncing along the bottom.

Treasure Hunter.description: Fish don't escape while collecting treasures. Also slightly increases the chance to find treasures.

Trap Bobber.description: Causes fish to escape slower when you aren't reeling them in.

Cork Bobber.description: Slightly increases the size of your "fishing bar".

Sturgeon.description: An ancient bottom-feeder with a dwindling population. Females can live up to 150 years.

Tiger Trout.description: A rare hybrid trout that cannot bear offspring of its own.

Bullhead.description: A relative of the catfish that eats a variety of foods off the lake bottom.

Tilapia.description: A primarily vegetarian fish that prefers warm water.

Chub.description: A common freshwater fish known for its voracious appetite.

Magnet.description: Increases the chance of finding treasures when fishing. However, fish aren't crazy about the taste.

Dorado.description: A fierce carnivore with brilliant orange scales.

Albacore.description: Prefers temperature "edges" where cool and warm water meet.

Shad.description: Lives in a school at sea, but returns to the rivers to spawn.

Lingcod.description: A fearsome predator that will eat almost anything it can cram into its mouth.

Halibut.description: A flat fish that lives on the ocean floor.

Hardwood.description: A special kind of wood with superior strength and beauty.

Crab Pot.description: Place it in the water, load it with bait, and check the next day to see if you've caught anything. Works in streams, lakes, and the ocean.

Lobster.description: A large ocean-dwelling crustacean with a strong tail.

Crayfish.description: A small freshwater relative of the lobster.

Crab.description: A marine crustacean with two powerful pincers.

Mussel.description: A common bivalve that often lives in clusters.

Shrimp.description: A scavenger that feeds off the ocean floor. Widely prized for its meat.

Snail.description: A wide-ranging mollusc that lives in a spiral shell.

Periwinkle.description: A tiny freshwater snail that lives in a blue shell.

Oyster.description: Constantly filters water to find food. In the process, it removes dangerous toxins from the environment.

Maple Syrup.description: A sweet syrup with a unique flavor.

Oak Resin.description: A sticky, fragrant substance derived from oak sap.

Pine Tar.description: A pungent substance derived from pine sap.

Chowder.description: A perfect way to warm yourself after a cold night at sea.

Fish Stew.description: It smells a lot like the sea. Tastes better, though.

Lobster Bisque.description: This delicate soup is a secret family recipe of Willy's.

Maple Bar.description: It's a sweet doughnut topped with a rich maple glaze.

Crab Cakes.description: Crab, bread crumbs, and egg formed into patties then fried to a golden brown.

Shrimp Cocktail.description: A sumptuous appetizer made with freshly-caught shrimp.

Woodskip.description: A very sensitive fish that can only live in pools deep in the forest.

Strawberry Seeds.description: Plant these in spring. Takes 8 days to mature, and keeps producing strawberries after that.

Rotten Plant.description: Decomposing organic material. It's slimy and unpleasant.

Omni Geode.description: A blacksmith can break this open for you. These geodes contain a wide variety of Minerals.

Slime.description: A shimmering, gelatinous glob with no smell.

Solar Essence.description: The glowing face is warm to the touch.

Mixed Seeds.description: There's a little bit of everything here. Plant them and see what grows!

Oil of Garlic.description: Drink this and weaker monsters will avoid you.

Wild Bait.description: A unique recipe from Linus that gives you a chance to catch two fish at once.

Glacierfish.description: Builds a nest on the underside of glaciers.

Battery Pack.description: It's fully charged with precious energy.

Lost Axe.description: Robin's been looking everywhere for it.

Lucky Purple Shorts.description: Better not inspect these too closely.

Berry Basket.description: The fibers are stained with berry juice.

Golden Coconut.description: This is one tough nut to crack, but a professional might be able to break it open.

Void Salmon.description: A salmon, twisted by void energy. The fresh meat is jet black, but rapidly turns pink when exposed to air.

Slimejack.description: He's coated in a very thick layer of slime. He keeps slipping out of your hands!

Pearl.description: A rare treasure from the sea.

Midnight Squid.description: A strange and mysterious denizen of the ocean's twilight depths.

Spook Fish.description: The huge eyes can detect the faint silhouettes of prey.

Blobfish.description: This odd creature floats above the ocean floor, consuming any edible material in its path.

Wedding Ring.description: An old Zuzu City tradition... It's used to ask for another farmer's hand in marriage.

Cactus Seeds.description: Can only be grown indoors. Takes 12 days to mature, and then produces fruit every 3 days.

Tree Fertilizer.description: Sprinkle on a wild tree to ensure rapid growth, even in winter. Doesn't work on fruit trees.

Dinosaur Mayonnaise.description: It's thick and creamy, with a vivid green hue. It smells like grass and leather.

Void Ghost Pendant.description: It's symbolic to the shadow people. As a gift, it signifies the desire to move in together as friends.

Movie Ticket.description: Admits one to the movie theater. Giving this to a friend invites them to the movies with you.

Crabshell Ring.description: The top of the ring is made from enchanted crab shell.

Napalm Ring.description: When you defeat an enemy, they explode.

Roe.description: Fresh fish eggs. These can be aged in a preserves jar to bring out more flavor.

Squid Ink.description: Squid use this ink to confuse would-be predators.

Tea Leaves.description: The young leaves of the tea plant. Can be brewed into the popular, energizing beverage.

Fossilized Tail.description: This tail has a club-like feature at the tip.

Fossilized Leg.description: A thick and sturdy leg bone.

Fossilized Ribs.description: Long ago, these ribs protected the body of a large animal.

Snake Skull.description: A preserved skull that once belonged to a snake.

Snake Vertebrae.description: It appears this serpent may have been extremely flexible.

Mummified Bat.description: The delicate wings have been perfectly preserved.

Mummified Frog.description: This ancient frog may have lived in the jungle canopy.

Ginger.description: This sharp, spicy root is said to increase vitality.

Taro Root.description: This starchy root is one of the most ancient crops.

Taro Tuber.description: Plant these in warm weather. Takes 10 days to mature. Grows faster if planted near a body of water.

Pineapple.description: A sweet and tangy tropical treat.

Pineapple Seeds.description: Plant these in warm weather. Takes 14 days to mature, and keeps producing fruit after that.

Mango.description: A big, sweet tropical fruit with a unique flavor.

Mango Sapling.description: Takes 28 days to produce a mature Mango tree. Bears fruit in the summer, or all year round when planted on Ginger Island.

Stingray.description: Despite having a toxic stinger, these fish are shy and prefer to avoid humans.

Lionfish.description: An aggressive, predatory fish with venomous spines.

Blue Discus.description: A brightly colored tropical fish that is popular in aquariums.

Thorns Ring.description: When enemies damage you, they will take damage themselves.

Rustic Plank Floor.description: Place on the ground to create paths or to decorate your floors.

Stone Walkway Floor.description: Place on the ground to create paths or to decorate your floors.

Journal Scrap.description: A damp tattered page torn from an old journal...

Cinder Shard.description: You can feel a warm glow from within this stone.

Magma Cap.description: A very rare mushroom that lives next to pools of lava.

Dragon Tooth.description: These are rumored to be the teeth of ancient serpents. The enamel is made of pure iridium!

Curiosity Lure.description: Increases your chance to catch rare fish.

Tiger Slime Egg.description: Can be hatched in a slime incubator. Use with extreme caution!

Qi Gem.description: A special currency honored by Mr. Qi.

Lucky Ring.description: The lunar emblem is said to bring good luck to whoever wears it.

Hot Java Ring.description: Greatly increases your chance to find coffee drinks when slaying monsters.

Protection Ring.description: Stay invincible for a little while longer after taking damage.

Soul Sapper Ring.description: Gain a little bit of energy every time you slay a monster.

Phoenix Ring.description: Once a day, regain some health after being knocked out in combat.

War Memento.description: It's a faded photograph of a soldier...

Gourmet Tomato Salt.description: A rare, delicious and savory salt.

Stardew Valley Rose.description: A rose that reminds you of the valley. It smells heavenly.

Advanced TV Remote.description: It has more buttons than a regular remote. Perfect for the avid TV watcher!

Arctic Shard.description: This shard glows with an otherworldly blue light.

Fairy Dust.description: Sprinkle on kegs, furnaces, and other refining equipment to instantly receive their product.

Bug Steak.description: The last resort of the hungry cave diver.

Ectoplasm.description: A thick, slimy goop that the Wizard wants for some reason.

Prismatic Jelly.description: Harvested from the rare and elusive prismatic slime.

Quality Bobber.description: Boosts the quality of fish that you catch.

Monster Musk.description: Spray this on to draw more monsters out of hiding.

Fiber Seeds.description: Plant these in any season. Does not require watering. Harvest with the scythe. Takes 7 days to grow.

Warp Totem: Island.description: Warp directly to Ginger Island. Consumed on use.

Immunity Band.description: The top of the ring is made from enchanted purple wool.

Glowstone Ring.description: Emits a constant light, and also increases your radius for collecting items.

Qi Fruit.description: Mr. Qi has challenged you to ship 500 of these strange melons.

Qi Bean.description: Plant these in any season. Water every day to produce a Qi Fruit. Takes 4 days to mature.

Mushroom Tree Seed.description: Place this on your farm to plant a mushroom tree.

Warp Totem: Qi's Arena.description: Warp to Qi's Arena. Be prepared for a challenge!.

Fireworks (Red).description: An old tradition for celebrations and festivities. Handle with care!

Fireworks (Purple).description: An old tradition for celebrations and festivities. Handle with care!

Fireworks (Green).description: An old tradition for celebrations and festivities. Handle with care!

Galaxy Soul.description: Forge 3 of these into a Galaxy weapon to unleash its final form.

Pierre's Missing Stocklist.description: Pierre might be interested in this.

Son of Crimsonfish.description: He hatched in the warm summer water, and followed in the footsteps of his father.

Ms. Angler.description: Uses a bioluminescent dangler to attract prey.

Legend II.description: The successor to the original Legend.

Radioactive Carp.description: A carp that spent one too many years in toxic sludge.

Glacierfish Jr..description: The original Glacierfish had a son...

Ginger Ale.description: A zesty soda known for its soothing effect on the stomach.

Banana Pudding.description: A creamy dessert with a wonderful tropical flavor.

Mango Sticky Rice.description: Sweet mango and coconut transforms this rice into something very special.

Poi.description: A traditional food with a delicate, sweet flavor when eaten fresh.

Tropical Curry.description: An exotic, fragrant curry served in a pineapple bowl.

Magic Bait.description: Allows you to catch fish from any season, time, or weather, from whichever type of water you cast into.

Radioactive Ore.description: It's glowing with dangerous energy... Can be smelted into bars.

Radioactive Bar.description: Known by the Zuzu City Safety Commission to cause irreversible bodily harm.

Horse Flute.description: Playing this flute will summon your horse. Only works outdoors.

Enricher.description: Place on a sprinkler and load with fertilizer to automatically apply it when planting seeds nearby.

Pressure Nozzle.description: Place on a sprinkler to increase its watering range.

Qi Seasoning.description: Just a dash will elevate any dish to extraordinary heights. Automatically applied when cooking.

Hyper Speed-Gro.description: Greatly stimulates leaf production. Guaranteed to increase growth rate by at least 33%. Mix into tilled soil.

Deluxe Fertilizer.description: Greatly improves soil quality, increasing your chance to grow quality crops. Mix into tilled soil.

Deluxe Retaining Soil.description: This soil has a 100% chance of staying watered overnight. Mix into tilled soil.

Cookout Kit.description: Use this to create a cooking campfire, allowing you to cook on-the-go!

Golden Egg.description: A very rare and special egg with a solid gold shell.
